metadata.name: Harmony #2
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Harmony' is somewhat inspired by the beautiful stain glass window designs of Frank Lloyd Wright (1867-1959).

Each 'Harmony' output is an attempt to find beauty (harmony) within the chaos created by a swirl of colors, shapes, lines and curves.

To download a 1500x2000px PNG:
Click/tap 'open', then click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear.

metadata.name: dreams #56
metadata.description:
As in a dream, this representation flows, changes direction and evolves.
Each piece represents one different dream. Calm down, nightmares, crossroads, triumphs, longings, forgotten memories, hopes, disappointments... Some have two faces, one light and one dark where sleep flows. Others have a central theme from where our dream is born or dies, in hope or in despair. Others, just flow.

--

Created with p5.js
Diego Pintos, Aug 2022.

metadata.name: Expression #17
metadata.description:
Face can be a canvas, painted with emotion and thought. Each expression tells a story, a tale waiting to be sought. From wrinkles to lines and creases, the face is a storybook, revealing secrets and emotions that we try to overlook. A smile can light up a room, bringing joy to those nearby, while a frown can darken any space and cause one to ask why. The eyes are said to be the windows to the soul that lies within, revealing the truth and deepest secrets that we try to keep hidden. Whether it's love, anger, fear or sadness, our face will always express, the feelings we hold within us and the thoughts we repress. So take a moment and read the faces that you see, for they may hold a story that's waiting to be set free.
_

Open / live mode / fullscreen view :
* press [s] on keyboard to save or download in PNG format

_

metadata.name: Vinciō #60
metadata.description:
"Vinciō", a means of binding, fastening, band, bond, rope, cord, fetter and tie.
This piece is a complex convergence of lines that eventually creates a unique pattern. There are different colors with light and dark backgrounds as well as different dimensions and styles.

This work can be printed in large dimensions,
so to see the artwork in higher quality, open it in live view and add “&res=1 to 10” to the URL.

The preview is automatically captured after 25 seconds of the animation.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: EcoPatterns #16
metadata.description:
This project is an invitation to see nature as an inspiring source through its complex and elegant patterns. The structures of a leaf, the symmetry of a flower, or the harmonious multicolored combinations can be inexhaustible resources for the mind of a generative artist eager to reproduce so much beauty around them.
Made entirely in p5.js

metadata.name: The Great Annihilator #88
metadata.description:
One day you wake up,
All words are meaningless
And you can feel the light inside your mouth
Where everything were assembled and annihilated
Swallow the air, swallow all particle
A taste of burnt metal and ethyl
One thousand years of living souls
And you, are no more



=========

Controls:

[1] Set resolution to 716 x 1024px (default)

[2] Set resolution to 1433 x 2048px

[3] Set resolution to 2688 x 3840px

* The presets above are suitable for screen viewing up to 4k screen resolution. To set a custom resolution for printing and other purpose, add &res=[desired resolution] at the end of the URL. It will set the height of the image, and the width will be calculated automatically at 0.7 ratio. For example to get a resolution of 4911 x 7016px (about the size of A2 paper), add &res=7016 as URL parameter.

[c] Capture a screenshot at rendered resolution


Notes:

* This project use shaders that relies on GPU. Hi-res output may slow down your device. Since it also utilize GPU instance for thumbnail rendering, expect longer time for every iterations to be signed by fx(hash).

* If 'glitching' occurs or the composition behaves differently at different resolution, just refresh the page to reset it.

Made with cables.gl, a node-based webgl environment

XALTED 2023

metadata.name: Hydro Gen #5
metadata.description:
Against the backdrop of texts about valuing water, Hydro Gen charts the ecological devastation and eventual revival of the Tisza river following what has been called one of the gravest environmental disasters in central Europe since Chernobyl.

Nature and humans here are bound within a single frame — havoc in the ecological system activates the breakdown of meaning in the human signifying system of language, but hidden in the wave of ecological disaster is a (re)generative love poem to water that bears witness to its multifaceted beauty and power. A second poem is generated as a soundtrack based on the displayed background text.

- - - - - CLICK TO START SOUND - - - - -

Hydro Gen is a collaborative work conceptualized and developed over the course of one week as part of NFT DEB Generative Dimensions 2022 Hackathon and Conference.

Kalen Iwamoto, lead artist, director

Vitalii Shumanskyi, lead programmer

Nayven Vignette, audio programmer

Tamás Béke, data analysis and visualization

metadata.name: Supernal Memories #291
metadata.description:
With its layered bursts of color, light, and shadow, Supernal Memories carries an underlying message of optimism through its harmony of seeming dualities – hard and soft, familiar and surprising, expression and introspection.

Each newly generated circle brings its own energy, creating layered groups of light that sometimes resemble phenomena like nebula, lightning sprites, and auras – ethereal whispers of something remembered. 

Supernal Memories is an invitation to observe the forms & feel of each piece without labeling their qualities, to contemplate the infinite possibilities of the universe, and to explore the depths of your imagination.


--

Created by Diego Pintos @DondiegoTez
Creative collaboration with Tender @tender_art

To get a high resolution file, add "&print=14000" to the end of the live URL / hash, using any resolution number that fits your needs. Press 's' to save the file when it is done loading.

Press 'p' to continue the animation for another variation.

100% code, made with p5.js
